      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Scaling back or tightening work requirements is the most direct way to address the disincentive problem. These policies are designed to ensure that the reward for working always outweighs the benefit of remaining on government support. The goal of a functional system is to provide a floor, not a hammock, so tying benefits strictly to active participation is the common economic solution.",
